com.inqwell.any.client

Class AnyTreeModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.client.AnyTreeModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, CellEditor, CellEditorListener, TreeCellEditor, TreeCellRenderer, TreeModel
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AnyTreeTableModel

    public class AnyTreeModel
extends Object
implements TreeModel, TreeCellRenderer, TreeCellEditor, CellEditorListener
    A TreeModel implementation that maps the Any framework's hierarchical structures to the TreeModel interface. Each level in a tree view is described by a TreeLevel implementation and most Tree Model functionality is delegated there.

    A given JTree can only have a single renderer and editor, so this class fulfills those requirements also, requesting the appropriate components from the relevant TreeLevel.

    Version:
    $Revision: 1.4 $
    Author:
    $Author: sanderst $

      • translateEvent

        public AnyTreeModel.AnyTreeModelEvent translateEvent(Event e,
                                                     JTable table,
                                                     JTree tree)
                                              throws AnyException
        Translate the Inq structure event into a TreeModelEvent which may then be dispatched to this model's registered TreeModelListeners.
        Parameters:
        e - the Inq structure event
        r - an optional RenderInfo that, if supplied, must satisfy the Inq event in the case of updates in order for the TreeModelEvent to be dispatched. Structural changes are always dispatched. This facility supports the TreeTable concept, whereby update events may not be applicable to the rendering tree, rather to the other columns in the view.
        Throws:
        AnyException
